      <div class="msgContentFrame">3000 TP Doomspikes hurt things real good. <br /> <br />Only thing is, I have better uses for my TP, i.e. Skull Sundering and Feinting every possible opportunity.  Having to use Light Thrust, only getting 20 HP as opposed to the 170 I was hoping for, after missing with a missed ferocity -&gt; bloodbath -&gt; Doomspike really sucks; I would much rather use skewer, miss and lose ferocity but still have the TP to use Skull Sunder and get another shot to earn 2/3 the HP I would have gotten if Skewer had hit.  1000 TP Skewer does about as much damage as a 2000 TP Doomspike (I've actually seen it do more). <br /> <br />In group situations where straight damage dealing is the goal, those 3000 TP Doomspikes have a home.  When soloing, I have found my survivability is much greater using Skewer as opposed to Doomspike.  Only problem with skewer is those annoying goats and dodos still obnoxiously follow you around, daring you to use an AoE TP skill.</div>
